UID:artivism-amplifiers-fellowship-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260626T212248Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260701
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260702
SUMMARY:Deadline: Artivism & Amplifiers Fellowship 2026
DESCRIPTION:The Artivism & Amplifiers (A&A) Fellowship pairs young climate 
 leaders from the Global North and Global South to co-create multimedia cam
 paigns\, exhibits\, and installations for the Creative Climate Awards 2027
 . Over six months\, fellows build skills in intercultural collaboration\, 
 climate storytelling\, and community engagement\, supported by expert work
 shops and creative mentors. The program is open to speakers of English\, S
 panish\, French\, and Portuguese. Fellows receive a USD 1\,000 stipend upo
 n completion. The organizers strongly encourage applications from people m
 ost impacted by the climate crisis\, including those from the global major
 ity\, Indigenous\, LGBTQIA+\, immigrant\, and diaspora communities\, and p
 eople with disabilities. Applications close Wednesday 1 July 2026 at 9am G
 MT+2.\n\nOrganisation: Human Impacts Institute\nLocation: Global\; pairs y
 oung climate leaders from the Global North and Global South. Open to speak
 ers of English\, Spanish\, French\, and Portuguese.\nAward: USD 1\,000 sti
 pend upon completion. Supported by expert workshops and creative mentors.\
 nDuration: Six-month program.\n\nMore: https://www.humanimpactsinstitute.o
 rg/opportunities
URL:https://www.humanimpactsinstitute.org/opportunities
LOCATION:Global\; pairs young climate leaders from the Global North and Glo
 bal South. Open to speakers of English\, Spanish\, French\, and Portuguese
 .
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:exploratorium-artist-in-residence-2026-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260626T212248Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260629
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260630
SUMMARY:Deadline: Exploratorium Artist-in-Residence Program 2026-2027
DESCRIPTION:Since its inception in 1974\, the Exploratorium's Artist-in-Res
 idence Program (AIR) has grown to include hundreds of artists and performe
 rs. The museum works with individuals and artist groups who are drawn to c
 ollaboration\, interested in interdisciplinary dialogue\, and open to deve
 loping new working methods. Projects have taken countless forms\, such as 
 multimedia performances\, theatrical productions\, animated filmmaking\, i
 mmersive installations\, walking tours\, and online projects. The program 
 allows artists to embed within the unique culture of the institution\, aff
 ords access to a dynamic and distinct staff\, and provides opportunities f
 or cross-pollination with a diverse public. While the museum allows room f
 or variance\, residencies typically unfold over two years and include both
  an exploratory and a project-development phase. The AIR program is an opp
 ortunity for artists to begin their residency with a sense of curiosity an
 d experimentation rather than a fully formed idea\, and to work in a co-cr
 eative manner with the Exploratorium. Applicants should be inherently curi
 ous and deeply invested in inquiry as part of their practice. AIRs receive
  a USD 15\,000 annual stipend\, support for travel\, project management an
 d financial support for residency projects\, and access to Exploratorium f
 acilities and staff expertise. APPLICATION TIMELINE: the form opened 20 Ma
 y 2026 with a no-cost early-bird period\; a USD 35 regular application fee
  applies from 10 June 2026\; last day to submit is 29 June 2026\; finalist
 s notified and interviews scheduled September 2026\; notifications sent to
  all applicants November 2026. Apply for the 2026-2027 program at the Expl
 oratorium AIR page.\n\nOrganisation: Exploratorium\nLocation: San Francisc
 o\, California\, United States. Residency is embedded within the Explorato
 rium\; includes access to its facilities and staff.\nAward: USD 15\,000 an
 nual stipend\, plus support for travel\, project management\, and financia
 l support for residency projects\, and access to Exploratorium facilities 
 and staff expertise.\nDuration: Residencies typically unfold over two year
 s\, including an exploratory phase and a project-development phase (room f
 or variance).\n\nMore: https://www.exploratorium.edu/arts/artist-residence
URL:https://www.exploratorium.edu/arts/artist-residence
LOCATION:San Francisco\, California\, United States. Residency is embedded 
 within the Exploratorium\; includes access to its facilities and staff.
END:VEVENT
