 \, recognises outstanding projects preserving and promoting European Jewis
 h cultural heritage. It is awarded across five categories: Shared Historie
 s\, Heritage for Dialogue\, Living Heritage\, Cross-border Cooperation and
  Shared Narratives\, and Next Generation/Youth Engagement and Education. A
 WARD: €10\,000 per Grand Prix winner (one per category\, five in total)\
 ; up to 25 finalists receive recognition. ELIGIBILITY: legal or natural pe
